    {"text": "Fall Armyworm (Spodoptera frugiperda) affects Maize. Symptoms: window pane feeding on leaves, frass in whorl. Control: Spinetoram 11.7% SC @ 0.5 ml/L water. Biological: release Trichogramma cards @ 50,000/ha.", "source": "ICAR Pest Alert", "category": "pest"},
    {"text": "Tomato Leaf Curl Virus is spread by whitefly (Bemisia tabaci). Management: yellow sticky traps, neem oil spray 3%, remove infected plants. Avoid planting near tobacco fields.", "source": "ICAR Pest Alert", "category": "pest"},
